  "texts": [
    "proposed a blockchain-based trustworthy medical data sharing framework in edge computing environments.",
    "The framework leveraged blockchain both to store the cryptographic digests of medical data and for distributed and secure key generation for Ciphertext-Policy Attribute-Based Encryption (CP-ABE) [31].In their study, Zaghloul et al.",
    "reported a novel distributed multilevel EMR management scheme, which used blockchain to address security concerns.",
    "The scheme also enabled the selective sharing of medical records that belonged to different levels of a hierarchical institution among staff members [32].Table 1 shows the key findings of some schemes in the literature for achieving an efficient healthcare service process based on blockchain technology.",
    "Technical backgroundThis section discusses techniques that are used in our proposed scheme."
  ],
